  "texts": [
    "Interestingly, the papers in the literature sample often define specific implementations of DEXs, such as AMMs, without first explaining what a DEX is.",
    "When DEXs are defined, it is often in the context of distinguishing them from CEXs, without explicitly outlining what defines a CEX (e.g., Berg et al., 2022; Falakshahi et al., 2021; Fritsch, 2021; Jeong et al., 2023).",
    "Furthermore, there are cases where terms such as DeFi and DEXs, although conceptually related, are still used interchangeably (Aigner & Dhaliwal, 2021; Shah et al., 2023).",
    "Overall, CEXs are defined much less frequently than DEXs.",
    "Only 27 out of 89 papers, or about 30% of all papers in the literature sample, provide a definition for CEXs."
  ],
